		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Cinematic techniques</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="rellink noprint relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Filmmaking" title="Filmmaking">Filmmaking</a></div>
<p><b>Cinematic techniques</b> are methods employed by <a href="/wiki/Film_director" title="Film director">film makers</a> to communicate meaning, entertain, and to produce a particular emotional or <a href="/wiki/Psychology" title="Psychology">psychological</a> response in an audience.</p>
